#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn24:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 24 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 24 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn24:0.2"
msgid "Rathavinītasutta "
msgstr "Prepared Chariots "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn24:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn24:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Comm says jatibhumi means the Buddha’s native district. I don’t think so. The word occurs at AN 6.54, Pvr 14, Ja 537, and Ja 546, and nowhere does it have any other sense than the expected “ones’ native district”.
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn24:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā jātibhūmakā bhikkhū jātibhūmiyaṃ vassaṃvuṭṭhā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then several mendicants who had completed the rainy season residence in their native land went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.146, sc2
msgctxt "mn24:2.2"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhikkhave, jātibhūmiyaṃ jātibhūmakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ evaṃ sambhāvito: "
msgstr "“In your native land, mendicants, which of the native mendicants is esteemed in this way: "

msgctxt "mn24:2.3"
msgid "‘attanā ca appiccho appicchakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca santuṭṭho santuṭṭhikathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca pavivitto pavivekakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca asaṃsaṭṭho asaṃsaggakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca āraddhavīriyo vīriyārambhakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca sīlasampanno sīlasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca samādhisampanno samādhisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca paññāsampanno paññāsampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca vimuttisampanno vimuttisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, ovādako viññāpako sandassako samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnan’”ti? "
msgstr "‘Personally having few wishes, they speak to the mendicants on having few wishes. Personally having contentment, seclusion, aloofness, energy, ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom, they speak to the mendicants on all these things. They’re an adviser and instructor, one who educates, encourages, fires up, and inspires their spiritual companions.’” "

# NOTE: Does this mean “son of the lady who recited the Vedas”?
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn24:2.4"
msgid "“Puṇṇo nāma, bhante, āyasmā mantāṇiputto jātibhūmiyaṃ jātibhūmakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ evaṃ sambhāvito: "
msgstr "“Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta, sir, is esteemed in this way in our native land.” "

msgctxt "mn24:2.5"
msgid "‘attanā ca appiccho appicchakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca santuṭṭho … pe … ovādako viññāpako sandassako samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc3
msgctxt "mn24:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Sāriputta was meditating not far from the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn24:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then he thought: "

# NOTE: Last phrase omitted by BB.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn24:3.3"
msgid "“lābhā āyasmato puṇṇassa mantāṇiputtassa, suladdhalābhā āyasmato puṇṇassa mantāṇiputtassa, "
msgstr "“Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta is fortunate, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn24:3.4"
msgid "yassa viññū sabrahmacārī satthu sammukhā anumassa anumassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, tañca satthā abbhanumodati. "
msgstr "in that his sensible spiritual companions praise him point by point in the presence of the Teacher, and that the Teacher seconds that appreciation. "

msgctxt "mn24:3.5"
msgid "Appeva nāma mayampi kadāci karahaci āyasmatā puṇṇena mantāṇiputtena saddhiṃ samāgaccheyyāma, appeva nāma siyā kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti. "
msgstr "Hopefully, some time or other I’ll get to meet Venerable Puṇṇa, and we can have a discussion.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, sc4
msgctxt "mn24:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā rājagahe yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi. "
msgstr "When the Buddha had stayed in Rājagaha as long as he wished, he set out for Sāvatthī. "

msgctxt "mn24:4.2"
msgid "Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi tadavasari. "
msgstr "Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Sāvatthī, "

msgctxt "mn24:4.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "where he stayed in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "mn24:4.4"
msgid "Assosi kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto: “bhagavā kira sāvatthiṃ anuppatto; sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme”ti. "
msgstr "Puṇṇa heard that the Buddha had arrived at Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, sc5
msgctxt "mn24:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then he set his lodgings in order and, taking his bowl and robe, set out for Sāvatthī. "

msgctxt "mn24:5.2"
msgid "Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi jetavanaṃ anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāmo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Eventually he came to Sāvatthī and Jeta’s Grove. He went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. "

msgctxt "mn24:5.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi. "
msgstr "The Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired him with a Dhamma talk. "

msgctxt "mn24:5.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena andhavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya. "
msgstr "Then, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, Puṇṇa got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right. Then he went to the Dark Forest for the day’s meditation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, pts-vp-pli1.147, sc6
msgctxt "mn24:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a certain mendicant went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn24:6.2"
msgid "“yassa kho tvaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, puṇṇassa nāma bhikkhuno mantāṇiputtassa abhiṇhaṃ kittayamāno ahosi, so bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena andhavanaṃ tena pakkanto divāvihārāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, the mendicant named Puṇṇa, of whom you have often spoken so highly, after being inspired by a talk of the Buddha’s, left for the Dark Forest for the day’s meditation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc7
msgctxt "mn24:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto taramānarūpo nisīdanaṃ ādāya āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi sīsānulokī. "
msgstr "Sāriputta quickly grabbed his sitting cloth and followed behind Puṇṇa, keeping sight of his head. "

msgctxt "mn24:7.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Puṇṇa plunged deep into the Dark Forest and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation. "

msgctxt "mn24:7.3"
msgid "Āyasmāpi kho sāriputto andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "And Sāriputta did likewise. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, sc8
msgctxt "mn24:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā puṇṇena mantāṇiputtena saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Puṇṇa, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn24:8.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to Puṇṇa: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc9
msgctxt "mn24:9.1"
msgid "“Bhagavati no, āvuso, brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Reverend, is our spiritual life lived under the Buddha?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "mn24:9.2"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "mn24:9.3"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of ethics?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn24:9.4"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Certainly not.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "mn24:9.5"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Then is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of mind?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "mn24:9.6"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Certainly not.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "mn24:9.7"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of view?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "mn24:9.8"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Certainly not.” "

# NOTE: Cf vitareyya ogham, the basic metaphor is to move over or across, not to defeat.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "mn24:9.9"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Then is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification through overcoming doubt?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "mn24:9.10"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Certainly not.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "mn24:9.11"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision of the variety of paths?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "mn24:9.12"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Certainly not.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "mn24:9.13"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Then is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision of the practice?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "mn24:9.14"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Certainly not.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "mn24:9.15"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "mn24:9.16"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Certainly not.” "

