#. REF: sc29
msgctxt "mn24:11.4"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
msgctxt "mn24:11.5"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "mn24:11.6"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc32
msgctxt "mn24:11.7"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc33
msgctxt "mn24:11.8"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc34
msgctxt "mn24:11.9"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc35
msgctxt "mn24:11.10"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "mn24:11.11"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc37
msgctxt "mn24:11.12"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc38
msgctxt "mn24:11.13"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti? "
msgstr "“Is purification of knowledge and vision extinguishment by not grasping?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc39
msgctxt "mn24:11.14"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Certainly not.” "

# NOTE: BB has “to be attained without these states”, but this seems to be unwarranted. I am not sure if this is just an amplification, or whether it reads the -ehi as causal. However aññatra usually takes the ablative and that is the case here. Thanissaro gets this right.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc40
msgctxt "mn24:11.15"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, aññatra imehi dhammehi anupādāparinibbānan”ti? "
msgstr "“Then is extinguishment by not grasping something apart from these things?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc41
msgctxt "mn24:11.16"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Certainly not.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc42
msgctxt "mn24:12.1"
msgid "“‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi. "
msgstr "“When asked each of these questions, you answered, ‘Certainly not.’ "

msgctxt "mn24:12.2"
msgid "‘Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:12.3"
msgid "‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:12.4"
msgid "kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:12.5"
msgid "maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:12.6"
msgid "paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:12.7"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:12.8"
msgid "‘Kiṃ panāvuso, aññatra imehi dhammehi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:12.9"
msgid "Yathākathaṃ panāvuso, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti? "
msgstr "How then should we see the meaning of this statement?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, sc43
#. VAR: paññapeyya → paññāpessa (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn24:13.1"
msgid "“Sīlavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya. "
msgstr "“If the Buddha had declared purification of ethics to be extinguishment by not grasping, he would have declared that which has grasping to be extinguishment by not grasping. … "

msgctxt "mn24:13.2"
msgid "Cittavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:13.3"
msgid "Diṭṭhivisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:13.4"
msgid "Kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:13.5"
msgid "Maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:13.6"
msgid "Paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:13.7"
msgid "Ñāṇadassanavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya. "
msgstr "If the Buddha had declared purification of knowledge and vision to be extinguishment by not grasping, he would have declared that which has grasping to be extinguishment by not grasping. "

msgctxt "mn24:13.8"
msgid "Aññatra ce, āvuso, imehi dhammehi anupādāparinibbānaṃ abhavissa, puthujjano parinibbāyeyya. "
msgstr "But if extinguishment by not grasping was something apart from these things, an ordinary person would become extinguished. "

msgctxt "mn24:13.9"
msgid "Puthujjano hi, āvuso, aññatra imehi dhammehi. "
msgstr "For an ordinary person lacks these things. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya14
msgctxt "mn24:14.1"
msgid "Tena hāvuso, upamaṃ te karissāmi; "
msgstr "Well then, reverend, I shall give you a simile. "

msgctxt "mn24:14.2"
msgid "upamāyapidhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti. "
msgstr "For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.149, sc44
msgctxt "mn24:14.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasantassa sākete kiñcideva accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ uppajjeyya. "
msgstr "Suppose that, while staying in Sāvatthī, King Pasenadi of Kosala had some urgent business come up in Sāketa. "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-relay-chariots-and-relays-of-chariots-and-trained-chariots/3894
msgctxt "mn24:14.4"
msgid "Tassa antarā ca sāvatthiṃ antarā ca sāketaṃ satta rathavinītāni upaṭṭhapeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "Now, between Sāvatthī and Sāketa seven prepared chariots were stationed ready for him. "

msgctxt "mn24:14.5"
msgid "Atha kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sāvatthiyā nikkhamitvā antepuradvārā paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya, paṭhamena rathavinītena dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya. "
msgstr "Then Pasenadi, having departed Sāvatthī, mounted the first prepared chariot by the gate of the royal compound. The first prepared chariot would bring him to the second, where he’d dismount and mount the second chariot. "

msgctxt "mn24:14.6"
msgid "Dutiyena rathavinītena tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya. "
msgstr "The second prepared chariot would bring him to the third … "

msgctxt "mn24:14.7"
msgid "Tatiyena rathavinītena catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya. "
msgstr "The third prepared chariot would bring him to the fourth … "

msgctxt "mn24:14.8"
msgid "Catutthena rathavinītena pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya. "
msgstr "The fourth prepared chariot would bring him to the fifth … "

msgctxt "mn24:14.9"
msgid "Pañcamena rathavinītena chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya. "
msgstr "The fifth prepared chariot would bring him to the sixth … "

msgctxt "mn24:14.10"
msgid "Chaṭṭhena rathavinītena sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya. "
msgstr "The sixth prepared chariot would bring him to the seventh, where he’d dismount and mount the seventh chariot. "

msgctxt "mn24:14.11"
msgid "Sattamena rathavinītena sāketaṃ anupāpuṇeyya antepuradvāraṃ. "
msgstr "The seventh prepared chariot would bring him to the gate of the royal compound of Sāketa. "

msgctxt "mn24:14.12"
msgid "Tamenaṃ antepuradvāragataṃ samānaṃ mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "And when he was at the gate, friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would ask him: "

msgctxt "mn24:14.13"
msgid "‘iminā tvaṃ, mahārāja, rathavinītena sāvatthiyā sāketaṃ anuppatto antepuradvāran’ti? "
msgstr "‘Great king, did you come to Sāketa from Sāvatthī by this prepared chariot?’ "

msgctxt "mn24:14.14"
msgid "Kathaṃ byākaramāno nu kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sammā byākaramāno byākareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "If asked this, how should King Pasenadi rightly reply?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc45
msgctxt "mn24:14.15"
msgid "“Evaṃ byākaramāno kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sammā byākaramāno byākareyya: "
msgstr "“The king should reply: "

#. VAR: uppajji → uppajjati (mr)
msgctxt "mn24:14.16"
msgid "‘idha me sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasantassa sākete kiñcideva accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ uppajji. "
msgstr "‘Well, while staying in Sāvatthī, I had some urgent business come up in Sāketa. "

msgctxt "mn24:14.17"
msgid "Tassa me antarā ca sāvatthiṃ antarā ca sāketaṃ satta rathavinītāni upaṭṭhapesuṃ. "
msgstr "Now, between Sāvatthī and Sāketa seven prepared chariots were stationed ready for me. "

msgctxt "mn24:14.18"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ sāvatthiyā nikkhamitvā antepuradvārā paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ. "
msgstr "Then, having departed Sāvatthī, I mounted the first prepared chariot by the gate of the royal compound. "

msgctxt "mn24:14.19"
msgid "Paṭhamena rathavinītena dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ. "
msgstr "The first prepared chariot brought me to the second, where I dismounted and mounted the second chariot. … "

msgctxt "mn24:14.20"
msgid "Dutiyena rathavinītena tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:14.21"
msgid "Tatiyena rathavinītena catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:14.22"
msgid "Catutthena rathavinītena pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:14.23"
msgid "Pañcamena rathavinītena chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:14.24"
msgid "Chaṭṭhena rathavinītena sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ. "
msgstr "The sixth prepared chariot brought me to the seventh, where I dismounted and mounted the seventh chariot. "

msgctxt "mn24:14.25"
msgid "Sattamena rathavinītena sāketaṃ anuppatto antepuradvāran’ti. "
msgstr "The seventh prepared chariot brought me to the gate of the royal compound of Sāketa.’ "

msgctxt "mn24:14.26"
msgid "Evaṃ byākaramāno kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sammā byākaramāno byākareyyā”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how King Pasenadi should rightly reply.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15, pts-vp-pli1.150, sc46
msgctxt "mn24:15.1"
msgid "“Evameva kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhi yāvadeva cittavisuddhatthā, cittavisuddhi yāvadeva diṭṭhivisuddhatthā, diṭṭhivisuddhi yāvadeva kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhatthā, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi yāvadeva maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhatthā, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi yāvadeva paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhatthā, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi yāvadeva ñāṇadassanavisuddhatthā, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi yāvadeva anupādāparinibbānatthā. "
msgstr "“In the same way, reverend, purification of ethics is only for the sake of purification of mind. Purification of mind is only for the sake of purification of view. Purification of view is only for the sake of purification through overcoming doubt. Purification through overcoming doubt is only for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision of the variety of paths. Purification of knowledge and vision of the variety of paths is only for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision of the practice. Purification of knowledge and vision of the practice is only for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision. Purification of knowledge and vision is only for the sake of extinguishment by not grasping. "

msgctxt "mn24:15.2"
msgid "Anupādāparinibbānatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti. "
msgstr "The spiritual life is lived under the Buddha for the sake of extinguishment by not grasping.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16, sc47
msgctxt "mn24:16.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Sāriputta said to Puṇṇa, "

msgctxt "mn24:16.2"
msgid "“konāmo āyasmā, kathañca panāyasmantaṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti? "
msgstr "“What is the venerable’s name? And how are you known among your spiritual companions?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn24:16.3"
msgid "“Puṇṇoti kho me, āvuso, nāmaṃ; "
msgstr "“Reverend, my name is Puṇṇa. "

msgctxt "mn24:16.4"
msgid "mantāṇiputtoti ca pana maṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti. "
msgstr "And I am known as Mantāṇiputta among my spiritual companions.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn24:16.5"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, reverend, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "mn24:16.6"
msgid "Yathā taṃ sutavatā sāvakena sammadeva satthusāsanaṃ ājānantena, evameva āyasmatā puṇṇena mantāṇiputtena gambhīrā gambhīrapañhā anumassa anumassa byākatā. "
msgstr "Venerable Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta has answered each deep question point by point, as a learned disciple who rightly understands the teacher’s instructions. "

msgctxt "mn24:16.7"
msgid "Lābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ, suladdhalābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ, "
msgstr "It is fortunate for his spiritual companions, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn24:16.8"
msgid "ye āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ labhanti dassanāya, labhanti payirūpāsanāya. "
msgstr "that they get to see Venerable Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta and pay homage to him. "

#. VAR: Celaṇḍukena → velaṇḍukena (s1-3) | celaṇḍakena (mr) | celaṇḍupekena (?)
msgctxt "mn24:16.9"
msgid "Celaṇḍukena cepi sabrahmacārī āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ muddhanā pariharantā labheyyuṃ dassanāya, labheyyuṃ payirūpāsanāya, tesampi lābhā tesampi suladdhaṃ, amhākampi lābhā amhākampi suladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ labhāma dassanāya, labhāma payirūpāsanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Even if they only got to see him and pay respects to him by carrying him around on their heads on a roll of cloth, it would still be very fortunate for them! And it’s fortunate for me, so very fortunate, that I get to see the venerable and pay homage to him.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, pts-vp-pli1.151, sc48
msgctxt "mn24:17.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Puṇṇa said to Sāriputta, "

msgctxt "mn24:17.2"
msgid "“ko nāmo āyasmā, kathañca panāyasmantaṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti? "
msgstr "“What is the venerable’s name? And how are you known among your spiritual companions?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn24:17.3"
msgid "“Upatissoti kho me, āvuso, nāmaṃ; "
msgstr "“Reverend, my name is Upatissa. "

msgctxt "mn24:17.4"
msgid "sāriputtoti ca pana maṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti. "
msgstr "And I am known as Sāriputta among my spiritual companions.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: bho → kho (mr)
msgctxt "mn24:17.5"
msgid "“Satthukappena vata kira, bho, sāvakena saddhiṃ mantayamānā na jānimha: "
msgstr "“Goodness! I had no idea I was consulting with *the* Venerable Sāriputta, the disciple who is fit to be compared with the Teacher himself! "

msgctxt "mn24:17.6"
msgid "‘āyasmā sāriputto’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn24:17.7"
msgid "Sace hi mayaṃ jāneyyāma ‘āyasmā sāriputto’ti, ettakampi no nappaṭibhāseyya. "
msgstr "If I’d known, I wouldn’t have said so much. "

msgctxt "mn24:17.8"
msgid "Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso. "
msgstr "It’s incredible, reverend, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "mn24:17.9"
msgid "Yathā taṃ sutavatā sāvakena sammadeva satthusāsanaṃ ājānantena, evameva āyasmatā sāriputtena gambhīrā gambhīrapañhā anumassa anumassa pucchitā. "
msgstr "Venerable Sāriputta has asked each deep question point by point, as a learned disciple who rightly understands the teacher’s instructions. "

msgctxt "mn24:17.10"
msgid "Lābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ suladdhalābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ, "
msgstr "It is fortunate for his spiritual companions, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn24:17.11"
msgid "ye āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ labhanti dassanāya, labhanti payirūpāsanāya. "
msgstr "that they get to see Venerable Sāriputta and pay homage to him. "

msgctxt "mn24:17.12"
msgid "Celaṇḍukena cepi sabrahmacārī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ muddhanā pariharantā labheyyuṃ dassanāya, labheyyuṃ payirūpāsanāya, tesampi lābhā tesampi suladdhaṃ, amhākampi lābhā amhākampi suladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ labhāma dassanāya, labhāma payirūpāsanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Even if they only got to see him and pay respects to him by carrying him around on their heads on a roll of cloth, it would still be very fortunate for them! And it’s fortunate for me, so very fortunate, that I get to see the venerable and pay homage to him.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc49
msgctxt "mn24:17.13"
msgid "Itiha te ubhopi mahānāgā aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ samanumodiṃsūti. "
msgstr "And so these two spiritual giants agreed with each others’ fine words. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn24:17.14"
msgid "Rathavinītasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

